<item>
            <title>[MNG-1355] Infinity Loop in DefaultMavenProjectBuilder.assembleLineage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-1355</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In my open-source project (&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.projxperts.com/mmm/trunk/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.projxperts.com/mmm/trunk/&lt;/a&gt;) I get an java.lang.StackOverflowError when I can mvn.&lt;br/&gt;
This seems to have something to do with the fact that the toplevel project has a subproject, that again has a subproject.&lt;br/&gt;
When I say subproject, I mean that it is declared as module in the parent pom.xml and its pom.xml defines the parent.&lt;br/&gt;
